  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1 - \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b86\u0b95\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Interim budget to be tabled in Parliament in August - Govt",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet Spokesperson Minister Bandula Gunawardena said that an interim budget will be submitted to Parliament by August to temporarily suspend development programs and provide relief to the people.",
        "The weekly press conference to announce the cabinet decisions was held on Tuesday. During this, a question was raised regarding the fact that the current President Ranil Wickremesinghe had said that the Interim Budget would be submitted soon when he was sworn in as the Prime Minister. While replying to this, the minister said the above.",
        "He further mentioned, 'Currently all the estimates for the essential expenditure for the ministries have been received.",
        "It is necessary to review all these and proceed with the allocation of funds in the Interim Budget. The interim-budget will be tabled in Parliament soon after the completion of those activities, by August.' said.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe made a special address to the nation on the 16th after being sworn in as Prime Minister on the 12th of May following the May 9 riots.",
        "In the said special speech, he mentioned that it is planned to present a new budget instead of the development budget presented for this year and it has been decided to present it as a concession budget.",
        "It was also informed that in the said Interim Budget Plan, the development projects will be temporarily suspended and the funds allocated for them will be used to provide relief to the people.",
        "About two months have passed since this was reported, but no action has been taken. It is noteworthy that when the question about this was raised yesterday, the Minister replied as above."
      ],
